Our food bank partners, such as Houston Food Bank, have been working to provide, prepare, and package shelf-stable groceries for vulnerable populations in their communities. We are honored to support their work with our delivery services.
Houston Food Bank
3 June at 09:01 ·
Houston Food Bank has teamed up with Amazon.com to deliver shelf-stable groceries directly to the doorsteps of Senior Citizens who have been disproportionately impacted by COVID-19.
Amazon will leverage its transportation network of Amazon Flex drivers to make contactless, doorstep deliveries. Amazon’s collaboration with Houston Food Bank is part of its commitment to deliver more than six million meals across the U.S. to underserved and vulnerable populations.
Thank you Amazon for being a great community partner during a time where help is needed the most. #foodforbetterlives
